## ⚠️ Risks & Tradeoffs

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|------------|
| **Cloud API doesn't support bulk/incremental endpoint** | Phase 2 blocked — can't sync efficiently | Build the Laravel endpoint first. Alternatively, iterate individual employee calls (slower but works). |
| **SQLite on SD card — write endurance** | SD card wear from frequent writes | Use WAL mode, batch writes, minimize write frequency. Consider USB SSD for production. |
| **Stale local data** | Employee changes in cloud not reflected immediately | 5-min sync interval is acceptable. Add manual "force sync" WS command for admin use. |
| **Database corruption** | Power loss during write could corrupt SQLite | Enable WAL mode. Add DB integrity check on startup. Keep backup of last known-good state. |
| **Increased Python memory usage** | Loading all org employees into SQLite | SQLite is disk-based, not in-memory. Negligible impact even with 10K+ employees. |
| **Dev mode regression** | Frontend changes may break dev simulation | Keep dev mode mock responses in `EnterID.jsx` aligned with new event types. |

